  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>prevalence of metabolic syndrome (MetS)</measure>
    <description>MetS will be diagnosed according to NCEP ATP III with the Asian-Pacific abdominal obesity criterion (≥90 cm in men, ≥85 cm in women)
3 or more of the following criteria
fasting plasma glucose &gt;= 100 mg/dl or drug use to treat elevated glucose
serum triglyceride (TG) &gt;= 150 mg/dl or drug use to treat elevated TG
HDL cholesterol level &lt; 40mg /dl in males, &lt; 50 mg/dl in female or drug use to treat low HDL
Systolic BP &gt;=130 mmHg, diastolic BP &gt;=85 or drug use to treat hypertension
Abdominal obesity : above described</description>
  </primary_outcome>
